      "writtenOn": "2019-12-06T22:19:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Alright -- Now, maybe to be consistent with Buildbucket\u0027s `critical`, this could potentially be a buildbucket `Trinary` value. In luci/cq/api/config/v2/cq.proto there\u0027s also an equivalent `Toggle` value.\n\nAnd for a message type like Trinary (or Toggle...), it seems like maybe that\u0027s something that could be in luci/common/proto/...\n\nBut actually, I think Trinary may be unnecessary here. I can see how for a config, you may want to have an \"unset\" value, which allows us to change the default behavior for projects that haven\u0027t explicitly specified a value, but for a specific CQ tryjob, it seems like the tryjob is either blocking or not, there\u0027s not really meaning for \"UNSET\". So plain old-fashioned bool here may be OK?",
